        "content": "<p>Is it impossible to refer inductively to the type being defined when using <code>structure</code>?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">inductive</span> <span class=\"n\">Wind</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"bp\">→</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">sup</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">head</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">tail</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">head</span> <span class=\"bp\">→</span> <span class=\"n\">Wind</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Wind</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This type works fine, but if I try to convert it to a structure so I can use e.g. field projections,</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">structure</span> <span class=\"n\">Wstr</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"bp\">→</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">head</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">tail</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">head</span> <span class=\"bp\">→</span> <span class=\"n\">Wstr</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I get an error about <code>Wstr</code> not being in scope.  Do I just have to use <code>inductive</code> even though it has only one constructor, and write all my projections and so forth manually?  Or is there some additional syntax I'm missing?  The manual says that <code>structure</code> is just sugar on top of <code>inductive</code>, so I expected to be able to do this.  Or can I perhaps define an <code>inductive</code> type such that Lean recognizes it as a structure and lets me use record syntax and things?</p>",
